    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>WATER SUPPLY GRANTS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Elsa Brenner</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Brenner, Elsa</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>New York State announces grants totaling $6 million to improve drinking water suppply programs in 36 counties, including $233,000 to Westchester, $218,000 to Putnam, $374,000 to Dutchess and $115,000 to Rockland (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>State grants totaling $6 million will be allotted to improve drinking water supply programs in 36 counties and New York City. Westchester will receive $233,000; Putnam, $218,000; Dutchess, $374,000; and Rockland, $115,000. The grants will be used to help local health departments bolster inspections of water systems, disinfect groundwater supplies, treat surface supplies and set standards for contaminants (radon, arsenic, and volatile organic chemicals).</p>
        <p>Elsa Brenner</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
